final_hyps.green: The green object is the Goal that the agent must reach.
final_hyps.brown: Brown objects are False Walls. The agent can move through False Walls.
final_hyps.yellow: The yellow object is a Key. The agent can pick up the Key by moving into its space. While holding the Key, the agent is colored purple.
final_hyps.cyan: The cyan object is a KeyDoor. When the agent moves onto this object, the KeyDoor opens and the Key is destroyed. The agent cannot move through the KeyDoor while it is closed.

solve_plan: First determine that the green object is the Goal object. Because the agent is not aligned with the goal object on the vertical axis (y=8), no action is needed for alignment. Next, the agent must pick up the yellow Key by moving RIGHT. Because the agent is at x=5 and the Key is at x=13, it must move RIGHT 13 - 5 = 8 times. Then, while holding the Key, the agent can move to reach the cyan KeyDoor (x=18) by moving RIGHT again. Because the agent will be at x=13 after picking up the Key, it must move RIGHT 18 - 13 = 5 times more. After opening the KeyDoor and destroying the Key, the agent can finally move to reach the goal (x=19) by moving RIGHT one last time.
